[{"location":"#MobiusSphere","page":"Home","title":"MobiusSphere","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Documentation for MobiusSphere.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"#MobiusSphere.rigid_to_Mobius","page":"Home","title":"MobiusSphere.rigid_to_Mobius","text":"rigid_to_Mobius(Q, T, source=[0, 1, im])\n\nGiven a 3D rotation Q (so, Q*Q'=Id and det(Q)=1) and a translation vector T, returns the Mobius transformation m corresponding to rotate the standard Riemann sphere by Q and translate it by T. That is, the map m is defined as m(z) = p_T(Q*p(z)+T), where p = stereo() is the standard stereographic projection and p_T = stereo(T) stereo projection centred at T.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"}]
